import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    top_jobs = data.groupby('job')['count'].sum().sort_values(ascending=False).head(10)
    top_jobs.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What are the top 10 most common job titles in the dataset?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    gender_distribution = data.groupby('sex')['count'].sum()
    plt.pie(gender_distribution, labels=gender_distribution.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title("What is the gender distribution across all job titles?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    data_grouped = data.groupby(['job', 'year'])['count'].sum().reset_index()
    
    for job in data_grouped['job'].unique():
        job_data = data_grouped[data_grouped['job'] == job]
        plt.plot(job_data['year'], job_data['count'], label=job)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Individuals')
    plt.title('How has the number of individuals in each job title changed over time?')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    job_gender_count = data.groupby(['job', 'sex'])['count'].sum().unstack()
    job_gender_count.plot(kind='bar', stacked=True, ax=plt.gca())
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of job titles by gender?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
